9 // This pass implements a simple loop unroller. It works best when loops have ----
10 // been canonicalized by the -indvars pass, allowing it to determine the trip ----
11 // counts of loops easily. ----
12 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

333 /// Figure out if the loop is worth full unrolling. ----
334 /// ----
335 /// Complete loop unrolling can make some loads constant, and we need to know ----
336 /// if that would expose any further optimization opportunities. This routine ----
337 /// estimates this optimization. It computes cost of unrolled loop ----
338 /// (UnrolledCost) and dynamic cost of the original loop (RolledDynamicCost). By ----
339 /// dynamic cost we mean that we won't count costs of blocks that are known not ----
340 /// to be executed (i.e. if we have a branch in the loop and we know that at the ----
341 /// given iteration its condition would be resolved to true, we won't add up the ----
342 /// cost of the 'false'-block). ----
343 /// \returns Optional value, holding the RolledDynamicCost and UnrolledCost. If ----
344 /// the analysis failed (no benefits expected from the unrolling, or the loop is ----
345 /// too big to analyze), the returned value is std::nullopt. ----
346 static std::optional analyzeLoopUnrollCost( 0
347 const Loop *L, unsigned TripCount, DominatorTree &DT, ScalarEvolution &SE, ----
348 const SmallPtrSetImpl &EphValues, ----
349 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, unsigned MaxUnrolledLoopSize, ----
350 unsigned MaxIterationsCountToAnalyze) { ----
351 // We want to be able to scale offsets by the trip count and add more offsets ----
352 // to them without checking for overflows, and we already don't want to ----
353 // analyze *massive* trip counts, so we force the max to be reasonably small. ----
354 assert(MaxIterationsCountToAnalyze < 0
355 (unsigned)(std::numeric_limits::max() / 2) && ----
356 "The unroll iterations max is too large!"); ----
357 ----
358 // Only analyze inner loops. We can't properly estimate cost of nested loops ----
359 // and we won't visit inner loops again anyway. ----
360 if (!L->isInnermost()) 0
361 return std::nullopt; 0
362 ----
363 // Don't simulate loops with a big or unknown tripcount ----
364 if (!TripCount || TripCount > MaxIterationsCountToAnalyze) 0
365 return std::nullopt; 0
366 ----
367 SmallSetVector BBWorklist; 0
368 SmallSetVector, 4> ExitWorklist; 0
369 DenseMap SimplifiedValues; 0
370 SmallVector, 4> SimplifiedInputValues; 0
371 ----
372 // The estimated cost of the unrolled form of the loop. We try to estimate ----
373 // this by simplifying as much as we can while computing the estimate. ----
374 InstructionCost UnrolledCost = 0; 0
375 ----
376 // We also track the estimated dynamic (that is, actually executed) cost in ----
377 // the rolled form. This helps identify cases when the savings from unrolling ----
378 // aren't just exposing dead control flows, but actual reduced dynamic ----
379 // instructions due to the simplifications which we expect to occur after ----
380 // unrolling. ----
381 InstructionCost RolledDynamicCost = 0; 0
382 ----
383 // We track the simplification of each instruction in each iteration. We use ----
384 // this to recursively merge costs into the unrolled cost on-demand so that ----
385 // we don't count the cost of any dead code. This is essentially a map from ----
386 // to , but stored as a densely packed struct. ----
387 DenseSet InstCostMap; 0
388 ----
389 // A small worklist used to accumulate cost of instructions from each ----
390 // observable and reached root in the loop. ----
391 SmallVector CostWorklist; 0
392 ----
393 // PHI-used worklist used between iterations while accumulating cost. ----
394 SmallVector PHIUsedList; 0
395 ----
396 // Helper function to accumulate cost for instructions in the loop. ----
397 auto AddCostRecursively = [&](Instruction &RootI, int Iteration) { 0
398 assert(Iteration >= 0 && "Cannot have a negative iteration!"); 0
399 assert(CostWorklist.empty() && "Must start with an empty cost list"); 0
400 assert(PHIUsedList.empty() && "Must start with an empty phi used list"); 0
401 CostWorklist.push_back(&RootI); 0
402 TargetTransformInfo::TargetCostKind CostKind = ----
403 RootI.getFunction()->hasMinSize() ? 0
404 TargetTransformInfo::TCK_CodeSize : ----
405 TargetTransformInfo::TCK_SizeAndLatency; 0
406 for (;; --Iteration) { 0
407 do { ----
408 Instruction *I = CostWorklist.pop_back_val(); 0
409 ----
410 // InstCostMap only uses I and Iteration as a key, the other two values ----
411 // don't matter here. ----
412 auto CostIter = InstCostMap.find({I, Iteration, 0, 0}); 0
413 if (CostIter == InstCostMap.end()) 0
414 // If an input to a PHI node comes from a dead path through the loop ----
415 // we may have no cost data for it here. What that actually means is ----
416 // that it is free. ----
417 continue; 0
418 auto &Cost = *CostIter; 0
419 if (Cost.IsCounted) 0
420 // Already counted this instruction. ----
421 continue; 0
422 ----
423 // Mark that we are counting the cost of this instruction now. ----
424 Cost.IsCounted = true; 0
425 ----
426 // If this is a PHI node in the loop header, just add it to the PHI set. ----
427 if (auto *PhiI = dyn_cast(I)) 0
428 if (PhiI->getParent() == L->getHeader()) { 0
429 assert(Cost.IsFree && "Loop PHIs shouldn't be evaluated as they " 0
430 "inherently simplify during unrolling."); ----
431 if (Iteration == 0) 0
432 continue; 0
433 ----
434 // Push the incoming value from the backedge into the PHI used list ----
435 // if it is an in-loop instruction. We'll use this to populate the ----
436 // cost worklist for the next iteration (as we count backwards). ----
437 if (auto *OpI = dyn_cast( 0
438 PhiI->getIncomingValueForBlock(L->getLoopLatch()))) 0
439 if (L->contains(OpI)) 0
440 PHIUsedList.push_back(OpI); 0
441 continue; 0
442 } 0
443 ----
444 // First accumulate the cost of this instruction. ----
445 if (!Cost.IsFree) { 0
446 UnrolledCost += TTI.getInstructionCost(I, CostKind); 0
447 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Adding cost of instruction (iteration " 0
448 << Iteration << "): "); ----
449 LLVM_DEBUG(I->dump()); 0
450 } ----
451 ----
452 // We must count the cost of every operand which is not free, ----
453 // recursively. If we reach a loop PHI node, simply add it to the set ----
454 // to be considered on the next iteration (backwards!). ----
455 for (Value *Op : I->operands()) { 0
456 // Check whether this operand is free due to being a constant or ----
457 // outside the loop. ----
458 auto *OpI = dyn_cast(Op); 0
459 if (!OpI || !L->contains(OpI)) 0
460 continue; 0
461 ----
462 // Otherwise accumulate its cost. ----
463 CostWorklist.push_back(OpI); 0
464 } ----
465 } while (!CostWorklist.empty()); 0
466 ----
467 if (PHIUsedList.empty()) 0
468 // We've exhausted the search. ----
469 break; 0
470 ----
471 assert(Iteration > 0 && 0
472 "Cannot track PHI-used values past the first iteration!"); ----
473 CostWorklist.append(PHIUsedList.begin(), PHIUsedList.end()); 0
474 PHIUsedList.clear(); 0
475 } 0
476 }; 0
477 ----
478 // Ensure that we don't violate the loop structure invariants relied on by ----
479 // this analysis. ----
480 assert(L->isLoopSimplifyForm() && "Must put loop into normal form first."); 0
481 assert(L->isLCSSAForm(DT) && 0
482 "Must have loops in LCSSA form to track live-out values."); ----
483 ----
484 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Starting LoopUnroll profitability analysis...\n"); 0
485 ----
486 TargetTransformInfo::TargetCostKind CostKind = ----
487 L->getHeader()->getParent()->hasMinSize() ? 0
488 TargetTransformInfo::TCK_CodeSize : TargetTransformInfo::TCK_SizeAndLatency; 0
489 // Simulate execution of each iteration of the loop counting instructions, ----
490 // which would be simplified. ----
491 // Since the same load will take different values on different iterations, ----
492 // we literally have to go through all loop's iterations. ----
493 for (unsigned Iteration = 0; Iteration < TripCount; ++Iteration) { 0
494 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Analyzing iteration " << Iteration << "\n"); 0
495 ----
496 // Prepare for the iteration by collecting any simplified entry or backedge ----
497 // inputs. ----
498 for (Instruction &I : *L->getHeader()) { 0
499 auto *PHI = dyn_cast(&I); 0
500 if (!PHI) 0
501 break; 0
502 ----
503 // The loop header PHI nodes must have exactly two input: one from the ----
504 // loop preheader and one from the loop latch. ----
505 assert( 0
506 PHI->getNumIncomingValues() == 2 && ----
507 "Must have an incoming value only for the preheader and the latch."); ----
508 ----
509 Value *V = PHI->getIncomingValueForBlock( 0
510 Iteration == 0 ? L->getLoopPreheader() : L->getLoopLatch()); 0
511 if (Iteration != 0 && SimplifiedValues.count(V)) 0
512 V = SimplifiedValues.lookup(V); 0
513 SimplifiedInputValues.push_back({PHI, V}); 0
514 } ----
515 ----
516 // Now clear and re-populate the map for the next iteration. ----
517 SimplifiedValues.clear(); 0
518 while (!SimplifiedInputValues.empty()) 0
519 SimplifiedValues.insert(SimplifiedInputValues.pop_back_val()); 0
520 ----
521 UnrolledInstAnalyzer Analyzer(Iteration, SimplifiedValues, SE, L); 0
522 ----
523 BBWorklist.clear(); 0
524 BBWorklist.insert(L->getHeader()); 0
525 // Note that we *must not* cache the size, this loop grows the worklist. ----
526 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx != BBWorklist.size(); ++Idx) { 0
527 BasicBlock *BB = BBWorklist[Idx]; 0
528 ----
529 // Visit all instructions in the given basic block and try to simplify ----
530 // it. We don't change the actual IR, just count optimization ----
531 // opportunities. ----
532 for (Instruction &I : *BB) { 0
533 // These won't get into the final code - don't even try calculating the ----
534 // cost for them. ----
535 if (isa(I) || EphValues.count(&I)) 0
536 continue; 0
537 ----
538 // Track this instruction's expected baseline cost when executing the ----
539 // rolled loop form. ----
540 RolledDynamicCost += TTI.getInstructionCost(&I, CostKind); 0
541 ----
542 // Visit the instruction to analyze its loop cost after unrolling, ----
543 // and if the visitor returns true, mark the instruction as free after ----
544 // unrolling and continue. ----
545 bool IsFree = Analyzer.visit(I); 0
546 bool Inserted = InstCostMap.insert({&I, (int)Iteration, 0
547 (unsigned)IsFree, ----
548 /*IsCounted*/ false}).second; 0
549 (void)Inserted; ----
550 assert(Inserted && "Cannot have a state for an unvisited instruction!"); 0
551 ----
552 if (IsFree) 0
553 continue; 0
554 ----
555 // Can't properly model a cost of a call. ----
556 // FIXME: With a proper cost model we should be able to do it. ----
557 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
558 const Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
559 if (!Callee || TTI.isLoweredToCall(Callee)) { 0
560 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't analyze cost of loop with call\n"); 0
561 return std::nullopt; 0
562 } ----
563 } ----
564 ----
565 // If the instruction might have a side-effect recursively account for ----
566 // the cost of it and all the instructions leading up to it. ----
567 if (I.mayHaveSideEffects()) 0
568 AddCostRecursively(I, Iteration); 0
569 ----
570 // If unrolled body turns out to be too big, bail out. ----
571 if (UnrolledCost > MaxUnrolledLoopSize) { 0
572 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Exceeded threshold.. exiting.\n" 0
573 << " UnrolledCost: " << UnrolledCost ----
574 << ", MaxUnrolledLoopSize: " << MaxUnrolledLoopSize ----
575 << "\n"); ----
576 return std::nullopt; 0
577 } ----
578 } ----
579 ----
580 Instruction *TI = BB->getTerminator(); 0
581 ----
582 auto getSimplifiedConstant = [&](Value *V) -> Constant * { 0
583 if (SimplifiedValues.count(V)) 0
584 V = SimplifiedValues.lookup(V); 0
585 return dyn_cast(V); 0
586 }; 0
587 ----
588 // Add in the live successors by first checking whether we have terminator ----
589 // that may be simplified based on the values simplified by this call. ----
590 BasicBlock *KnownSucc = nullptr; 0
591 if (BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast(TI)) { 0
592 if (BI->isConditional()) { 0
593 if (auto *SimpleCond = getSimplifiedConstant(BI->getCondition())) { 0
594 // Just take the first successor if condition is undef ----
595 if (isa(SimpleCond)) 0
596 KnownSucc = BI->getSuccessor(0); 0
597 else if (ConstantInt *SimpleCondVal = 0
598 dyn_cast(SimpleCond)) 0
599 KnownSucc = BI->getSuccessor(SimpleCondVal->isZero() ? 1 : 0); 0
600 } ----
601 } ----
602 } else if (SwitchInst *SI = dyn_cast(TI)) { 0
603 if (auto *SimpleCond = getSimplifiedConstant(SI->getCondition())) { 0
604 // Just take the first successor if condition is undef ----
605 if (isa(SimpleCond)) 0
606 KnownSucc = SI->getSuccessor(0); 0
607 else if (ConstantInt *SimpleCondVal = 0
608 dyn_cast(SimpleCond)) 0
609 KnownSucc = SI->findCaseValue(SimpleCondVal)->getCaseSuccessor(); 0
610 } ----
611 } ----
612 if (KnownSucc) { 0
613 if (L->contains(KnownSucc)) 0
614 BBWorklist.insert(KnownSucc); 0
615 else ----
616 ExitWorklist.insert({BB, KnownSucc}); 0
617 continue; 0
618 } ----
619 ----
620 // Add BB's successors to the worklist. ----
621 for (BasicBlock *Succ : successors(BB)) 0
622 if (L->contains(Succ)) 0
623 BBWorklist.insert(Succ); 0
624 else ----
625 ExitWorklist.insert({BB, Succ}); 0
626 AddCostRecursively(*TI, Iteration); 0
627 } ----
628 ----
629 // If we found no optimization opportunities on the first iteration, we ----
630 // won't find them on later ones too. ----
631 if (UnrolledCost == RolledDynamicCost) { 0
632 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " No opportunities found.. exiting.\n" 0
633 << " UnrolledCost: " << UnrolledCost << "\n"); ----
634 return std::nullopt; 0
635 } ----
636 } 0
637 ----
638 while (!ExitWorklist.empty()) { 0
639 BasicBlock *ExitingBB, *ExitBB; ----
640 std::tie(ExitingBB, ExitBB) = ExitWorklist.pop_back_val(); 0
641 ----
642 for (Instruction &I : *ExitBB) { 0
643 auto *PN = dyn_cast(&I); 0
644 if (!PN) 0
645 break; 0
646 ----
647 Value *Op = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(ExitingBB); 0
648 if (auto *OpI = dyn_cast(Op)) 0
649 if (L->contains(OpI)) 0
650 AddCostRecursively(*OpI, TripCount - 1); 0
651 } ----
652 } ----
653 ----
654 assert(UnrolledCost.isValid() && RolledDynamicCost.isValid() && 0
655 "All instructions must have a valid cost, whether the " ----
656 "loop is rolled or unrolled."); ----
657 ----
658 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Analysis finished:\n" 0
659 << "UnrolledCost: " << UnrolledCost << ", " ----
660 << "RolledDynamicCost: " << RolledDynamicCost << "\n"); ----
661 return {{unsigned(*UnrolledCost.getValue()), 0
662 unsigned(*RolledDynamicCost.getValue())}}; 0
663 } 0
664 ----
665 /// ApproximateLoopSize - Approximate the size of the loop. ----
666 InstructionCost llvm::ApproximateLoopSize( 0
667 const Loop *L, unsigned &NumCalls, bool &NotDuplicatable, bool &Convergent, ----
668 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, ----
669 const SmallPtrSetImpl &EphValues, unsigned BEInsns) { ----
670 CodeMetrics Metrics; 0
671 for (BasicBlock *BB : L->blocks()) 0
672 Metrics.analyzeBasicBlock(BB, TTI, EphValues); 0
673 NumCalls = Metrics.NumInlineCandidates; 0
674 NotDuplicatable = Metrics.notDuplicatable; 0
675 Convergent = Metrics.convergent; 0
676 ----
677 InstructionCost LoopSize = Metrics.NumInsts; 0
678 ----
679 // Don't allow an estimate of size zero. This would allows unrolling of loops ----
680 // with huge iteration counts, which is a compile time problem even if it's ----
681 // not a problem for code quality. Also, the code using this size may assume ----
682 // that each loop has at least three instructions (likely a conditional ----
683 // branch, a comparison feeding that branch, and some kind of loop increment ----
684 // feeding that comparison instruction). ----
685 if (LoopSize.isValid() && LoopSize < BEInsns + 1) 0
686 // This is an open coded max() on InstructionCost ----
687 LoopSize = BEInsns + 1; 0
688 ----
689 return LoopSize; 0
690 } 0
691 ----
692 // Returns the loop hint metadata node with the given name (for example, ----
693 // "llvm.loop.unroll.count"). If no such metadata node exists, then nullptr is ----
694 // returned. ----
695 static MDNode *getUnrollMetadataForLoop(const Loop *L, StringRef Name) { 0
696 if (MDNode *LoopID = L->getLoopID()) 0
697 return GetUnrollMetadata(LoopID, Name); 0
698 return nullptr; 0
699 } ----
700 ----
701 // Returns true if the loop has an unroll(full) pragma. ----
702 static bool hasUnrollFullPragma(const Loop *L) { 0
703 return getUnrollMetadataForLoop(L, "llvm.loop.unroll.full"); 0
704 } ----
705 ----
706 // Returns true if the loop has an unroll(enable) pragma. This metadata is used ----
707 // for both "#pragma unroll" and "#pragma clang loop unroll(enable)" directives. ----
708 static bool hasUnrollEnablePragma(const Loop *L) { 0
709 return getUnrollMetadataForLoop(L, "llvm.loop.unroll.enable"); 0
710 } ----
711 ----
712 // Returns true if the loop has an runtime unroll(disable) pragma. ----
713 static bool hasRuntimeUnrollDisablePragma(const Loop *L) { 0
714 return getUnrollMetadataForLoop(L, "llvm.loop.unroll.runtime.disable"); 0
715 } ----
716 ----
717 // If loop has an unroll_count pragma return the (necessarily ----
718 // positive) value from the pragma. Otherwise return 0. ----
719 static unsigned unrollCountPragmaValue(const Loop *L) { 0
720 MDNode *MD = getUnrollMetadataForLoop(L, "llvm.loop.unroll.count"); 0
721 if (MD) { 0
722 assert(MD->getNumOperands() == 2 && 0
723 "Unroll count hint metadata should have two operands."); ----
724 unsigned Count = ----
725 mdconst::extract(MD->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
726 assert(Count >= 1 && "Unroll count must be positive."); 0
727 return Count; 0
728 } ----
729 return 0; 0
730 } ----
731 ----
732 // Computes the boosting factor for complete unrolling. ----
733 // If fully unrolling the loop would save a lot of RolledDynamicCost, it would ----
734 // be beneficial to fully unroll the loop even if unrolledcost is large. We ----
735 // use (RolledDynamicCost / UnrolledCost) to model the unroll benefits to adjust ----
736 // the unroll threshold. ----
737 static unsigned getFullUnrollBoostingFactor(const EstimatedUnrollCost &Cost, 0
738 unsigned MaxPercentThresholdBoost) { ----
739 if (Cost.RolledDynamicCost >= std::numeric_limits::max() / 100) 0
740 return 100; 0
741 else if (Cost.UnrolledCost != 0) 0
742 // The boosting factor is RolledDynamicCost / UnrolledCost ----
743 return std::min(100 * Cost.RolledDynamicCost / Cost.UnrolledCost, 0
744 MaxPercentThresholdBoost); 0
745 else ----
746 return MaxPercentThresholdBoost; 0
747 } ----
748 ----
749 // Produce an estimate of the unrolled cost of the specified loop. This ----
750 // is used to a) produce a cost estimate for partial unrolling and b) to ----
751 // cheaply estimate cost for full unrolling when we don't want to symbolically ----
752 // evaluate all iterations. ----
753 class UnrollCostEstimator { ----
754 const unsigned LoopSize; ----
755 ----
756 public: ----
757 UnrollCostEstimator(Loop &L, unsigned LoopSize) : LoopSize(LoopSize) {} 0
758 ----
759 // Returns loop size estimation for unrolled loop, given the unrolling ----
760 // configuration specified by UP. ----
761 uint64_t ----
762 getUnrolledLoopSize(const TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences &UP, 0
763 const unsigned CountOverwrite = 0) const { ----
764 assert(LoopSize >= UP.BEInsns && 0
765 "LoopSize should not be less than BEInsns!"); ----
766 if (CountOverwrite) 0
767 return static_cast(LoopSize - UP.BEInsns) * CountOverwrite + 0
768 UP.BEInsns; 0
769 else ----
770 return static_cast(LoopSize - UP.BEInsns) * UP.Count + 0
771 UP.BEInsns; 0
772 } ----
773 }; ----
774 ----
775 static std::optional ----
776 shouldPragmaUnroll(Loop *L, const PragmaInfo &PInfo, 0
777 const unsigned TripMultiple, const unsigned TripCount, ----
778 const UnrollCostEstimator UCE, ----
779 const TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences &UP) { ----
780 ----
781 // Using unroll pragma ----
782 // 1st priority is unroll count set by "unroll-count" option. ----
783 ----
784 if (PInfo.UserUnrollCount) { 0
785 if (UP.AllowRemainder && 0
786 UCE.getUnrolledLoopSize(UP, (unsigned)UnrollCount) < UP.Threshold) 0
787 return (unsigned)UnrollCount; 0
788 } ----
789 ----
790 // 2nd priority is unroll count set by pragma. ----
791 if (PInfo.PragmaCount > 0) { 0
792 if ((UP.AllowRemainder || (TripMultiple % PInfo.PragmaCount == 0))) 0
793 return PInfo.PragmaCount; 0
794 } ----
795 ----
796 if (PInfo.PragmaFullUnroll && TripCount != 0) 0
797 return TripCount; 0
798 ----
799 // if didn't return until here, should continue to other priorties ----
800 return std::nullopt; 0
801 } ----
802 ----
803 static std::optional shouldFullUnroll( 0
804 Loop *L, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, DominatorTree &DT, ----
805 ScalarEvolution &SE, const SmallPtrSetImpl &EphValues, ----
806 const unsigned FullUnrollTripCount, const UnrollCostEstimator UCE, ----
807 const TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences &UP) { ----
808 assert(FullUnrollTripCount && "should be non-zero!"); 0
809 ----
810 if (FullUnrollTripCount > UP.FullUnrollMaxCount) 0
811 return std::nullopt; 0
812 ----
813 // When computing the unrolled size, note that BEInsns are not replicated ----
814 // like the rest of the loop body. ----
815 if (UCE.getUnrolledLoopSize(UP) < UP.Threshold) 0
816 return FullUnrollTripCount; 0
817 ----
818 // The loop isn't that small, but we still can fully unroll it if that ----
819 // helps to remove a significant number of instructions. ----
820 // To check that, run additional analysis on the loop. ----
821 if (std::optional Cost = analyzeLoopUnrollCost( 0
822 L, FullUnrollTripCount, DT, SE, EphValues, TTI, ----
823 UP.Threshold * UP.MaxPercentThresholdBoost / 100, 0
824 UP.MaxIterationsCountToAnalyze)) { 0
825 unsigned Boost = ----
826 getFullUnrollBoostingFactor(*Cost, UP.MaxPercentThresholdBoost); 0
827 if (Cost->UnrolledCost < UP.Threshold * Boost / 100) 0
828 return FullUnrollTripCount; 0
829 } ----
830 return std::nullopt; 0
831 } ----
832 ----
833 static std::optional ----
834 shouldPartialUnroll(const unsigned LoopSize, const unsigned TripCount, 0
835 const UnrollCostEstimator UCE, ----
836 const TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences &UP) { ----
837 ----
838 if (!TripCount) 0
839 return std::nullopt; 0
840 ----
841 if (!UP.Partial) { 0
842 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " will not try to unroll partially because " 0
843 << "-unroll-allow-partial not given\n"); ----
844 return 0; 0
845 } ----
846 unsigned count = UP.Count; 0
847 if (count == 0) 0
848 count = TripCount; 0
849 if (UP.PartialThreshold != NoThreshold) { 0
850 // Reduce unroll count to be modulo of TripCount for partial unrolling. ----
851 if (UCE.getUnrolledLoopSize(UP, count) > UP.PartialThreshold) 0
852 count = (std::max(UP.PartialThreshold, UP.BEInsns + 1) - UP.BEInsns) / 0
853 (LoopSize - UP.BEInsns); 0
854 if (count > UP.MaxCount) 0
855 count = UP.MaxCount; 0
856 while (count != 0 && TripCount % count != 0) 0
857 count--; 0
858 if (UP.AllowRemainder && count <= 1) { 0
859 // If there is no Count that is modulo of TripCount, set Count to ----
860 // largest power-of-two factor that satisfies the threshold limit. ----
861 // As we'll create fixup loop, do the type of unrolling only if ----
862 // remainder loop is allowed. ----
863 count = UP.DefaultUnrollRuntimeCount; 0
864 while (count != 0 && 0
865 UCE.getUnrolledLoopSize(UP, count) > UP.PartialThreshold) 0
866 count >>= 1; 0
867 } ----
868 if (count < 2) { 0
869 count = 0; 0
870 } ----
871 } else { ----
872 count = TripCount; 0
873 } ----
874 if (count > UP.MaxCount) 0
875 count = UP.MaxCount; 0
876 ----
877 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " partially unrolling with count: " << count << "\n"); 0
878 ----
879 return count; 0
880 } ----
881 // Returns true if unroll count was set explicitly. ----
882 // Calculates unroll count and writes it to UP.Count. ----
883 // Unless IgnoreUser is true, will also use metadata and command-line options ----
884 // that are specific to to the LoopUnroll pass (which, for instance, are ----
885 // irrelevant for the LoopUnrollAndJam pass). ----
886 // FIXME: This function is used by LoopUnroll and LoopUnrollAndJam, but consumes ----
887 // many LoopUnroll-specific options. The shared functionality should be ----
888 // refactored into it own function. ----
889 bool llvm::computeUnrollCount( 0
890 Loop *L, const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, DominatorTree &DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
891 AssumptionCache *AC, ----
892 ScalarEvolution &SE, const SmallPtrSetImpl &EphValues, ----
893 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE, unsigned TripCount, unsigned MaxTripCount, ----
894 bool MaxOrZero, unsigned TripMultiple, unsigned LoopSize, ----
895 TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences &UP, ----
896 TargetTransformInfo::PeelingPreferences &PP, bool &UseUpperBound) { ----
897 ----
898 UnrollCostEstimator UCE(*L, LoopSize); 0
899 ----
900 const bool UserUnrollCount = UnrollCount.getNumOccurrences() > 0; 0
901 const bool PragmaFullUnroll = hasUnrollFullPragma(L); 0
902 const unsigned PragmaCount = unrollCountPragmaValue(L); 0
903 const bool PragmaEnableUnroll = hasUnrollEnablePragma(L); 0
904 ----
905 const bool ExplicitUnroll = PragmaCount > 0 || PragmaFullUnroll || 0
906 PragmaEnableUnroll || UserUnrollCount; 0
907 ----
908 PragmaInfo PInfo(UserUnrollCount, PragmaFullUnroll, PragmaCount, ----
909 PragmaEnableUnroll); 0
910 // Use an explicit peel count that has been specified for testing. In this ----
911 // case it's not permitted to also specify an explicit unroll count. ----
912 if (PP.PeelCount) { 0
913 if (UnrollCount.getNumOccurrences() > 0) { 0
914 report_fatal_error("Cannot specify both explicit peel count and " 0
915 "explicit unroll count", /*GenCrashDiag=*/false); ----
916 } ----
917 UP.Count = 1; 0
918 UP.Runtime = false; 0
919 return true; 0
920 } ----
921 // Check for explicit Count. ----
922 // 1st priority is unroll count set by "unroll-count" option. ----
923 // 2nd priority is unroll count set by pragma. ----
924 if (auto UnrollFactor = shouldPragmaUnroll(L, PInfo, TripMultiple, TripCount, 0
925 UCE, UP)) { 0
926 UP.Count = *UnrollFactor; 0
927 ----
928 if (UserUnrollCount || (PragmaCount > 0)) { 0
929 UP.AllowExpensiveTripCount = true; 0
930 UP.Force = true; 0
931 } ----
932 UP.Runtime |= (PragmaCount > 0); 0
933 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
934 } else { ----
935 if (ExplicitUnroll && TripCount != 0) { 0
936 // If the loop has an unrolling pragma, we want to be more aggressive with ----
937 // unrolling limits. Set thresholds to at least the PragmaUnrollThreshold ----
938 // value which is larger than the default limits. ----
939 UP.Threshold = std::max(UP.Threshold, PragmaUnrollThreshold); 0
940 UP.PartialThreshold = 0
941 std::max(UP.PartialThreshold, PragmaUnrollThreshold); 0
942 } ----
943 } ----
944 ----
945 // 3rd priority is exact full unrolling. This will eliminate all copies ----
946 // of some exit test. ----
947 UP.Count = 0; 0
948 if (TripCount) { 0
949 UP.Count = TripCount; 0
950 if (auto UnrollFactor = shouldFullUnroll(L, TTI, DT, SE, EphValues, 0
951 TripCount, UCE, UP)) { 0
952 UP.Count = *UnrollFactor; 0
953 UseUpperBound = false; 0
954 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
955 } ----
956 } ----
957 ----
958 // 4th priority is bounded unrolling. ----
959 // We can unroll by the upper bound amount if it's generally allowed or if ----
960 // we know that the loop is executed either the upper bound or zero times. ----
961 // (MaxOrZero unrolling keeps only the first loop test, so the number of ----
962 // loop tests remains the same compared to the non-unrolled version, whereas ----
963 // the generic upper bound unrolling keeps all but the last loop test so the ----
964 // number of loop tests goes up which may end up being worse on targets with ----
965 // constrained branch predictor resources so is controlled by an option.) ----
966 // In addition we only unroll small upper bounds. ----
967 // Note that the cost of bounded unrolling is always strictly greater than ----
968 // cost of exact full unrolling. As such, if we have an exact count and ----
969 // found it unprofitable, we'll never chose to bounded unroll. ----
970 if (!TripCount && MaxTripCount && (UP.UpperBound || MaxOrZero) && 0
971 MaxTripCount <= UnrollMaxUpperBound) { 0
972 UP.Count = MaxTripCount; 0
973 if (auto UnrollFactor = shouldFullUnroll(L, TTI, DT, SE, EphValues, 0
974 MaxTripCount, UCE, UP)) { 0
975 UP.Count = *UnrollFactor; 0
976 UseUpperBound = true; 0
977 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
978 } ----
979 } ----
980 ----
981 // 5th priority is loop peeling. ----
982 computePeelCount(L, LoopSize, PP, TripCount, DT, SE, AC, UP.Threshold); 0
983 if (PP.PeelCount) { 0
984 UP.Runtime = false; 0
985 UP.Count = 1; 0
986 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
987 } ----
988 ----
989 // Before starting partial unrolling, set up.partial to true, ----
990 // if user explicitly asked for unrolling ----
991 if (TripCount) 0
992 UP.Partial |= ExplicitUnroll; 0
993 ----
994 // 6th priority is partial unrolling. ----
995 // Try partial unroll only when TripCount could be statically calculated. ----
996 if (auto UnrollFactor = shouldPartialUnroll(LoopSize, TripCount, UCE, UP)) { 0
997 UP.Count = *UnrollFactor; 0
998 ----
999 if ((PragmaFullUnroll || PragmaEnableUnroll) && TripCount && 0
1000 UP.Count != TripCount) 0
1001 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1002 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(DEBUG_TYPE, 0
1003 "FullUnrollAsDirectedTooLarge", ----
1004 L->getStartLoc(), L->getHeader()) 0
1005 << "Unable to fully unroll loop as directed by unroll pragma " ----
1006 "because " ----
1007 "unrolled size is too large."; 0
1008 }); ----
1009 ----
1010 if (UP.PartialThreshold != NoThreshold) { 0
1011 if (UP.Count == 0) { 0
1012 if (PragmaEnableUnroll) 0
1013 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1014 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(DEBUG_TYPE, 0
1015 "UnrollAsDirectedTooLarge", ----
1016 L->getStartLoc(), L->getHeader()) 0
1017 << "Unable to unroll loop as directed by unroll(enable) " ----
1018 "pragma " ----
1019 "because unrolled size is too large."; 0
1020 }); ----
1021 } ----
1022 } ----
1023 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
1024 } ----
1025 assert(TripCount == 0 && 0
1026 "All cases when TripCount is constant should be covered here."); ----
1027 if (PragmaFullUnroll) 0
1028 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1029 return OptimizationRemarkMissed( 0
1030 DEBUG_TYPE, "CantFullUnrollAsDirectedRuntimeTripCount", ----
1031 L->getStartLoc(), L->getHeader()) 0
1032 << "Unable to fully unroll loop as directed by unroll(full) " ----
1033 "pragma " ----
1034 "because loop has a runtime trip count."; 0
1035 }); ----
1036 ----
1037 // 7th priority is runtime unrolling. ----
1038 // Don't unroll a runtime trip count loop when it is disabled. ----
1039 if (hasRuntimeUnrollDisablePragma(L)) { 0
1040 UP.Count = 0; 0
1041 return false; 0
1042 } ----
1043 ----
1044 // Don't unroll a small upper bound loop unless user or TTI asked to do so. ----
1045 if (MaxTripCount && !UP.Force && MaxTripCount < UnrollMaxUpperBound) { 0
1046 UP.Count = 0; 0
1047 return false; 0
1048 } ----
1049 ----
1050 // Check if the runtime trip count is too small when profile is available. ----
1051 if (L->getHeader()->getParent()->hasProfileData()) { 0
1052 if (auto ProfileTripCount = getLoopEstimatedTripCount(L)) { 0
1053 if (*ProfileTripCount < FlatLoopTripCountThreshold) 0
1054 return false; 0
1055 else ----
1056 UP.AllowExpensiveTripCount = true; 0
1057 } ----
1058 } ----
1059 UP.Runtime |= PragmaEnableUnroll || PragmaCount > 0 || UserUnrollCount; 0
1060 if (!UP.Runtime) { 0
1061 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1062 dbgs() << " will not try to unroll loop with runtime trip count " ----
1063 << "-unroll-runtime not given\n"); ----
1064 UP.Count = 0; 0
1065 return false; 0
1066 } ----
1067 if (UP.Count == 0) 0
1068 UP.Count = UP.DefaultUnrollRuntimeCount; 0
1069 ----
1070 // Reduce unroll count to be the largest power-of-two factor of ----
1071 // the original count which satisfies the threshold limit. ----
1072 while (UP.Count != 0 && 0
1073 UCE.getUnrolledLoopSize(UP) > UP.PartialThreshold) 0
1074 UP.Count >>= 1; 0
1075 ----
1076 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1077 unsigned OrigCount = UP.Count; 0
1078 #endif ----
1079 ----
1080 if (!UP.AllowRemainder && UP.Count != 0 && (TripMultiple % UP.Count) != 0) { 0
1081 while (UP.Count != 0 && TripMultiple % UP.Count != 0) 0
1082 UP.Count >>= 1; 0
1083 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1084 dbgs() << "Remainder loop is restricted (that could architecture " ----
1085 "specific or because the loop contains a convergent " ----
1086 "instruction), so unroll count must divide the trip " ----
1087 "multiple, " ----
1088 << TripMultiple << ". Reducing unroll count from " << OrigCount ----
1089 << " to " << UP.Count << ".\n"); ----
1090 ----
1091 using namespace ore; ----
1092 ----
1093 if (unrollCountPragmaValue(L) > 0 && !UP.AllowRemainder) 0
1094 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1095 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(DEBUG_TYPE, 0
1096 "DifferentUnrollCountFromDirected", ----
1097 L->getStartLoc(), L->getHeader()) 0
1098 << "Unable to unroll loop the number of times directed by " ----
1099 "unroll_count pragma because remainder loop is restricted " ----
1100 "(that could architecture specific or because the loop " ----
1101 "contains a convergent instruction) and so must have an " ----
1102 "unroll " ----
1103 "count that divides the loop trip multiple of " 0
1104 << NV("TripMultiple", TripMultiple) << ". Unrolling instead " 0
1105 << NV("UnrollCount", UP.Count) << " time(s)."; 0
1106 }); ----
1107 } ----
1108 ----
1109 if (UP.Count > UP.MaxCount) 0
1110 UP.Count = UP.MaxCount; 0
1111 ----
1112 if (MaxTripCount && UP.Count > MaxTripCount) 0
1113 UP.Count = MaxTripCount; 0
1114 ----
1115 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " runtime unrolling with count: " << UP.Count 0
1116 << "\n"); ----
1117 if (UP.Count < 2) 0
1118 UP.Count = 0; 0
1119 return ExplicitUnroll; 0
1120 } ----
1121 ----
1122 static LoopUnrollResult ----
1123 tryToUnrollLoop(Loop *L, DominatorTree &DT, LoopInfo *LI, ScalarEvolution &SE, 0
1124 const TargetTransformInfo &TTI, AssumptionCache &AC, ----
1125 OptimizationRemarkEmitter &ORE, BlockFrequencyInfo *BFI, ----
1126 ProfileSummaryInfo *PSI, bool PreserveLCSSA, int OptLevel, ----
1127 bool OnlyFullUnroll, bool OnlyWhenForced, bool ForgetAllSCEV, ----
1128 std::optional ProvidedCount, ----
1129 std::optional ProvidedThreshold, ----
1130 std::optional ProvidedAllowPartial, ----
1131 std::optional ProvidedRuntime, ----
1132 std::optional ProvidedUpperBound, ----
1133 std::optional ProvidedAllowPeeling, ----
1134 std::optional ProvidedAllowProfileBasedPeeling, ----
1135 std::optional ProvidedFullUnrollMaxCount) { ----
1136 ----
1137 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Loop Unroll: F[" 0
1138 << L->getHeader()->getParent()->getName() << "] Loop %" ----
1139 << L->getHeader()->getName() << "\n"); ----
1140 TransformationMode TM = hasUnrollTransformation(L); 0
1141 if (TM & TM_Disable) 0
1142 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1143 ----
1144 // If this loop isn't forced to be unrolled, avoid unrolling it when the ----
1145 // parent loop has an explicit unroll-and-jam pragma. This is to prevent ----
1146 // automatic unrolling from interfering with the user requested ----
1147 // transformation. ----
1148 Loop *ParentL = L->getParentLoop(); 0
1149 if (ParentL != nullptr && 0
1150 hasUnrollAndJamTransformation(ParentL) == TM_ForcedByUser && 0
1151 hasUnrollTransformation(L) != TM_ForcedByUser) { 0
1152 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Not unrolling loop since parent loop has" 0
1153 << " llvm.loop.unroll_and_jam.\n"); ----
1154 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1155 } ----
1156 ----
1157 // If this loop isn't forced to be unrolled, avoid unrolling it when the ----
1158 // loop has an explicit unroll-and-jam pragma. This is to prevent automatic ----
1159 // unrolling from interfering with the user requested transformation. ----
1160 if (hasUnrollAndJamTransformation(L) == TM_ForcedByUser && 0
1161 hasUnrollTransformation(L) != TM_ForcedByUser) { 0
1162 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1163 dbgs() ----
1164 << " Not unrolling loop since it has llvm.loop.unroll_and_jam.\n"); ----
1165 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1166 } ----
1167 ----
1168 if (!L->isLoopSimplifyForm()) { 0
1169 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1170 dbgs() << " Not unrolling loop which is not in loop-simplify form.\n"); ----
1171 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1172 } ----
1173 ----
1174 // When automatic unrolling is disabled, do not unroll unless overridden for ----
1175 // this loop. ----
1176 if (OnlyWhenForced && !(TM & TM_Enable)) 0
1177 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1178 ----
1179 bool OptForSize = L->getHeader()->getParent()->hasOptSize(); 0
1180 unsigned NumInlineCandidates; ----
1181 bool NotDuplicatable; ----
1182 bool Convergent; ----
1183 TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences UP = gatherUnrollingPreferences( 0
1184 L, SE, TTI, BFI, PSI, ORE, OptLevel, ProvidedThreshold, ProvidedCount, ----
1185 ProvidedAllowPartial, ProvidedRuntime, ProvidedUpperBound, ----
1186 ProvidedFullUnrollMaxCount); ----
1187 TargetTransformInfo::PeelingPreferences PP = gatherPeelingPreferences( 0
1188 L, SE, TTI, ProvidedAllowPeeling, ProvidedAllowProfileBasedPeeling, true); ----
1189 ----
1190 // Exit early if unrolling is disabled. For OptForSize, we pick the loop size ----
1191 // as threshold later on. ----
1192 if (UP.Threshold == 0 && (!UP.Partial || UP.PartialThreshold == 0) && 0
1193 !OptForSize) 0
1194 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1195 ----
1196 SmallPtrSet EphValues; 0
1197 CodeMetrics::collectEphemeralValues(L, &AC, EphValues); 0
1198 ----
1199 InstructionCost LoopSizeIC = ----
1200 ApproximateLoopSize(L, NumInlineCandidates, NotDuplicatable, Convergent, 0
1201 TTI, EphValues, UP.BEInsns); ----
1202 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Loop Size = " << LoopSizeIC << "\n"); 0
1203 ----
1204 if (!LoopSizeIC.isValid()) { 0
1205 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Not unrolling loop which contains instructions" 0
1206 << " with invalid cost.\n"); ----
1207 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1208 } ----
1209 unsigned LoopSize = *LoopSizeIC.getValue(); 0
1210 ----
1211 if (NotDuplicatable) { 0
1212 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Not unrolling loop which contains non-duplicatable" 0
1213 << " instructions.\n"); ----
1214 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1215 } ----
1216 ----
1217 // When optimizing for size, use LoopSize + 1 as threshold (we use < Threshold ----
1218 // later), to (fully) unroll loops, if it does not increase code size. ----
1219 if (OptForSize) 0
1220 UP.Threshold = std::max(UP.Threshold, LoopSize + 1); 0
1221 ----
1222 if (NumInlineCandidates != 0) { 0
1223 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Not unrolling loop with inlinable calls.\n"); 0
1224 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1225 } ----
1226 ----
1227 // Find the smallest exact trip count for any exit. This is an upper bound ----
1228 // on the loop trip count, but an exit at an earlier iteration is still ----
1229 // possible. An unroll by the smallest exact trip count guarantees that all ----
1230 // branches relating to at least one exit can be eliminated. This is unlike ----
1231 // the max trip count, which only guarantees that the backedge can be broken. ----
1232 unsigned TripCount = 0; 0
1233 unsigned TripMultiple = 1; 0
1234 SmallVector ExitingBlocks; 0
1235 L->getExitingBlocks(ExitingBlocks); 0
1236 for (BasicBlock *ExitingBlock : ExitingBlocks) 0
1237 if (unsigned TC = SE.getSmallConstantTripCount(L, ExitingBlock)) 0
1238 if (!TripCount || TC < TripCount) 0
1239 TripCount = TripMultiple = TC; 0
1240 ----
1241 if (!TripCount) { 0
1242 // If no exact trip count is known, determine the trip multiple of either ----
1243 // the loop latch or the single exiting block. ----
1244 // TODO: Relax for multiple exits. ----
1245 BasicBlock *ExitingBlock = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
1246 if (!ExitingBlock || !L->isLoopExiting(ExitingBlock)) 0
1247 ExitingBlock = L->getExitingBlock(); 0
1248 if (ExitingBlock) 0
1249 TripMultiple = SE.getSmallConstantTripMultiple(L, ExitingBlock); 0
1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 // If the loop contains a convergent operation, the prelude we'd add ----
1253 // to do the first few instructions before we hit the unrolled loop ----
1254 // is unsafe -- it adds a control-flow dependency to the convergent ----
1255 // operation. Therefore restrict remainder loop (try unrolling without). ----
1256 // ----
1257 // TODO: This is quite conservative. In practice, convergent_op() ----
1258 // is likely to be called unconditionally in the loop. In this ----
1259 // case, the program would be ill-formed (on most architectures) ----
1260 // unless n were the same on all threads in a thread group. ----
1261 // Assuming n is the same on all threads, any kind of unrolling is ----
1262 // safe. But currently llvm's notion of convergence isn't powerful ----
1263 // enough to express this. ----
1264 if (Convergent) 0
1265 UP.AllowRemainder = false; 0
1266 ----
1267 // Try to find the trip count upper bound if we cannot find the exact trip ----
1268 // count. ----
1269 unsigned MaxTripCount = 0; 0
1270 bool MaxOrZero = false; 0
1271 if (!TripCount) { 0
1272 MaxTripCount = SE.getSmallConstantMaxTripCount(L); 0
1273 MaxOrZero = SE.isBackedgeTakenCountMaxOrZero(L); 0
1274 } ----
1275 ----
1276 // computeUnrollCount() decides whether it is beneficial to use upper bound to ----
1277 // fully unroll the loop. ----
1278 bool UseUpperBound = false; 0
1279 bool IsCountSetExplicitly = computeUnrollCount( 0
1280 L, TTI, DT, LI, &AC, SE, EphValues, &ORE, TripCount, MaxTripCount, MaxOrZero, ----
1281 TripMultiple, LoopSize, UP, PP, UseUpperBound); ----
1282 if (!UP.Count) 0
1283 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1284 ----
1285 if (PP.PeelCount) { 0
1286 assert(UP.Count == 1 && "Cannot perform peel and unroll in the same step"); 0
1287 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "PEELING loop %" << L->getHeader()->getName() 0
1288 << " with iteration count " << PP.PeelCount << "!\n"); ----
1289 ORE.emit([&]() { 0
1290 return OptimizationRemark(DEBUG_TYPE, "Peeled", L->getStartLoc(), 0
1291 L->getHeader()) 0
1292 << " peeled loop by " << ore::NV("PeelCount", PP.PeelCount) 0
1293 << " iterations"; 0
1294 }); ----
1295 ----
1296 ValueToValueMapTy VMap; 0
1297 if (peelLoop(L, PP.PeelCount, LI, &SE, DT, &AC, PreserveLCSSA, VMap)) { 0
1298 simplifyLoopAfterUnroll(L, true, LI, &SE, &DT, &AC, &TTI); 0
1299 // If the loop was peeled, we already "used up" the profile information ----
1300 // we had, so we don't want to unroll or peel again. ----
1301 if (PP.PeelProfiledIterations) 0
1302 L->setLoopAlreadyUnrolled(); 0
1303 return LoopUnrollResult::PartiallyUnrolled; 0
1304 } ----
1305 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1306 } 0
1307 ----
1308 // Do not attempt partial/runtime unrolling in FullLoopUnrolling ----
1309 if (OnlyFullUnroll && !(UP.Count >= MaxTripCount)) { 0
1310 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1311 dbgs() << "Not attempting partial/runtime unroll in FullLoopUnroll.\n"); ----
1312 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1313 } ----
1314 ----
1315 // At this point, UP.Runtime indicates that run-time unrolling is allowed. ----
1316 // However, we only want to actually perform it if we don't know the trip ----
1317 // count and the unroll count doesn't divide the known trip multiple. ----
1318 // TODO: This decision should probably be pushed up into ----
1319 // computeUnrollCount(). ----
1320 UP.Runtime &= TripCount == 0 && TripMultiple % UP.Count != 0; 0
1321 ----
1322 // Save loop properties before it is transformed. ----
1323 MDNode *OrigLoopID = L->getLoopID(); 0
1324 ----
1325 // Unroll the loop. ----
1326 Loop *RemainderLoop = nullptr; 0
1327 LoopUnrollResult UnrollResult = UnrollLoop( 0
1328 L, ----
1329 {UP.Count, UP.Force, UP.Runtime, UP.AllowExpensiveTripCount, 0
1330 UP.UnrollRemainder, ForgetAllSCEV}, 0
1331 LI, &SE, &DT, &AC, &TTI, &ORE, PreserveLCSSA, &RemainderLoop); ----
1332 if (UnrollResult == LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified) 0
1333 return LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1334 ----
1335 if (RemainderLoop) { 0
1336 std::optional RemainderLoopID = ----
1337 makeFollowupLoopID(OrigLoopID, {LLVMLoopUnrollFollowupAll, 0
1338 LLVMLoopUnrollFollowupRemainder}); ----
1339 if (RemainderLoopID) 0
1340 RemainderLoop->setLoopID(*RemainderLoopID); 0
1341 } ----
1342 ----
1343 if (UnrollResult != LoopUnrollResult::FullyUnrolled) { 0
1344 std::optional NewLoopID = ----
1345 makeFollowupLoopID(OrigLoopID, {LLVMLoopUnrollFollowupAll, 0
1346 LLVMLoopUnrollFollowupUnrolled}); ----
1347 if (NewLoopID) { 0
1348 L->setLoopID(*NewLoopID); 0
1349 ----
1350 // Do not setLoopAlreadyUnrolled if loop attributes have been specified ----
1351 // explicitly. ----
1352 return UnrollResult; 0
1353 } ----
1354 } ----
1355 ----
1356 // If loop has an unroll count pragma or unrolled by explicitly set count ----
1357 // mark loop as unrolled to prevent unrolling beyond that requested. ----
1358 if (UnrollResult != LoopUnrollResult::FullyUnrolled && IsCountSetExplicitly) 0
1359 L->setLoopAlreadyUnrolled(); 0
1360 ----
1361 return UnrollResult; 0
1362 } 0

1480 PreservedAnalyses LoopFullUnrollPass::run(Loop &L, LoopAnalysisManager &AM, 0
1481 LoopStandardAnalysisResults &AR, ----
1482 LPMUpdater &Updater) { ----
1483 // For the new PM, we can't use OptimizationRemarkEmitter as an analysis ----
1484 // pass. Function analyses need to be preserved across loop transformations ----
1485 // but ORE cannot be preserved (see comment before the pass definition). ----
1486 OptimizationRemarkEmitter ORE(L.getHeader()->getParent()); 0
1487 ----
1488 // Keep track of the previous loop structure so we can identify new loops ----
1489 // created by unrolling. ----
1490 Loop *ParentL = L.getParentLoop(); 0
1491 SmallPtrSet OldLoops; 0
1492 if (ParentL) 0
1493 OldLoops.insert(ParentL->begin(), ParentL->end()); 0
1494 else ----
1495 OldLoops.insert(AR.LI.begin(), AR.LI.end()); 0
1496 ----
1497 std::string LoopName = std::string(L.getName()); 0
1498 ----
1499 bool Changed = ----
1500 tryToUnrollLoop(&L, AR.DT, &AR.LI, AR.SE, AR.TTI, AR.AC, ORE, 0
1501 /*BFI*/ nullptr, /*PSI*/ nullptr, ----
1502 /*PreserveLCSSA*/ true, OptLevel, /*OnlyFullUnroll*/ true, 0
1503 OnlyWhenForced, ForgetSCEV, /*Count*/ std::nullopt, 0
1504 /*Threshold*/ std::nullopt, /*AllowPartial*/ false, 0
1505 /*Runtime*/ false, /*UpperBound*/ false, 0
1506 /*AllowPeeling*/ true, 0
1507 /*AllowProfileBasedPeeling*/ false, 0
1508 /*FullUnrollMaxCount*/ std::nullopt) != ----
1509 LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1510 if (!Changed) 0
1511 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
1512 ----
1513 // The parent must not be damaged by unrolling! ----
1514 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1515 if (ParentL) 0
1516 ParentL->verifyLoop(); 0
1517 #endif ----
1518 ----
1519 // Unrolling can do several things to introduce new loops into a loop nest: ----
1520 // - Full unrolling clones child loops within the current loop but then ----
1521 // removes the current loop making all of the children appear to be new ----
1522 // sibling loops. ----
1523 // ----
1524 // When a new loop appears as a sibling loop after fully unrolling, ----
1525 // its nesting structure has fundamentally changed and we want to revisit ----
1526 // it to reflect that. ----
1527 // ----
1528 // When unrolling has removed the current loop, we need to tell the ----
1529 // infrastructure that it is gone. ----
1530 // ----
1531 // Finally, we support a debugging/testing mode where we revisit child loops ----
1532 // as well. These are not expected to require further optimizations as either ----
1533 // they or the loop they were cloned from have been directly visited already. ----
1534 // But the debugging mode allows us to check this assumption. ----
1535 bool IsCurrentLoopValid = false; 0
1536 SmallVector SibLoops; 0
1537 if (ParentL) 0
1538 SibLoops.append(ParentL->begin(), ParentL->end()); 0
1539 else ----
1540 SibLoops.append(AR.LI.begin(), AR.LI.end()); 0
1541 erase_if(SibLoops, [&](Loop *SibLoop) { 0
1542 if (SibLoop == &L) { 0
1543 IsCurrentLoopValid = true; 0
1544 return true; 0
1545 } ----
1546 ----
1547 // Otherwise erase the loop from the list if it was in the old loops. ----
1548 return OldLoops.contains(SibLoop); 0
1549 }); ----
1550 Updater.addSiblingLoops(SibLoops); 0
1551 ----
1552 if (!IsCurrentLoopValid) { 0
1553 Updater.markLoopAsDeleted(L, LoopName); 0
1554 } else { ----
1555 // We can only walk child loops if the current loop remained valid. ----
1556 if (UnrollRevisitChildLoops) { 0
1557 // Walk *all* of the child loops. ----
1558 SmallVector ChildLoops(L.begin(), L.end()); 0
1559 Updater.addChildLoops(ChildLoops); 0
1560 } 0
1561 } ----
1562 ----
1563 return getLoopPassPreservedAnalyses(); 0
1564 } 0
1565 ----
1566 PreservedAnalyses LoopUnrollPass::run(Function &F, 0
1567 FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) { ----
1568 auto &LI = AM.getResult(F); 0
1569 // There are no loops in the function. Return before computing other expensive ----
1570 // analyses. ----
1571 if (LI.empty()) 0
1572 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
1573 auto &SE = AM.getResult(F); 0
1574 auto &TTI = AM.getResult(F); 0
1575 auto &DT = AM.getResult(F); 0
1576 auto &AC = AM.getResult(F); 0
1577 auto &ORE = AM.getResult(F); 0
1578 ----
1579 LoopAnalysisManager *LAM = nullptr; 0
1580 if (auto *LAMProxy = AM.getCachedResult(F)) 0
1581 LAM = &LAMProxy->getManager(); 0
1582 ----
1583 auto &MAMProxy = AM.getResult(F); 0
1584 ProfileSummaryInfo *PSI = ----
1585 MAMProxy.getCachedResult(*F.getParent()); 0
1586 auto *BFI = (PSI && PSI->hasProfileSummary()) ? 0
1587 &AM.getResult(F) : nullptr; 0
1588 ----
1589 bool Changed = false; 0
1590 ----
1591 // The unroller requires loops to be in simplified form, and also needs LCSSA. ----
1592 // Since simplification may add new inner loops, it has to run before the ----
1593 // legality and profitability checks. This means running the loop unroller ----
1594 // will simplify all loops, regardless of whether anything end up being ----
1595 // unrolled. ----
1596 for (const auto &L : LI) { 0
1597 Changed |= 0
1598 simplifyLoop(L, &DT, &LI, &SE, &AC, nullptr, false /* PreserveLCSSA */); 0
1599 Changed |= formLCSSARecursively(*L, DT, &LI, &SE); 0
1600 } ----
1601 ----
1602 // Add the loop nests in the reverse order of LoopInfo. See method ----
1603 // declaration. ----
1604 SmallPriorityWorklist Worklist; 0
1605 appendLoopsToWorklist(LI, Worklist); 0
1606 ----
1607 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
1608 // Because the LoopInfo stores the loops in RPO, we walk the worklist ----
1609 // from back to front so that we work forward across the CFG, which ----
1610 // for unrolling is only needed to get optimization remarks emitted in ----
1611 // a forward order. ----
1612 Loop &L = *Worklist.pop_back_val(); 0
1613 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1614 Loop *ParentL = L.getParentLoop(); 0
1615 #endif ----
1616 ----
1617 // Check if the profile summary indicates that the profiled application ----
1618 // has a huge working set size, in which case we disable peeling to avoid ----
1619 // bloating it further. ----
1620 std::optional LocalAllowPeeling = UnrollOpts.AllowPeeling; 0
1621 if (PSI && PSI->hasHugeWorkingSetSize()) 0
1622 LocalAllowPeeling = false; 0
1623 std::string LoopName = std::string(L.getName()); 0
1624 // The API here is quite complex to call and we allow to select some ----
1625 // flavors of unrolling during construction time (by setting UnrollOpts). ----
1626 LoopUnrollResult Result = tryToUnrollLoop( 0
1627 &L, DT, &LI, SE, TTI, AC, ORE, BFI, PSI, ----
1628 /*PreserveLCSSA*/ true, UnrollOpts.OptLevel, /*OnlyFullUnroll*/ false, ----
1629 UnrollOpts.OnlyWhenForced, UnrollOpts.ForgetSCEV, 0
1630 /*Count*/ std::nullopt, ----
1631 /*Threshold*/ std::nullopt, UnrollOpts.AllowPartial, ----
1632 UnrollOpts.AllowRuntime, UnrollOpts.AllowUpperBound, LocalAllowPeeling, ----
1633 UnrollOpts.AllowProfileBasedPeeling, UnrollOpts.FullUnrollMaxCount); ----
1634 Changed |= Result != LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified; 0
1635 ----
1636 // The parent must not be damaged by unrolling! ----
1637 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1638 if (Result != LoopUnrollResult::Unmodified && ParentL) 0
1639 ParentL->verifyLoop(); 0
1640 #endif ----
1641 ----
1642 // Clear any cached analysis results for L if we removed it completely. ----
1643 if (LAM && Result == LoopUnrollResult::FullyUnrolled) 0
1644 LAM->clear(L, LoopName); 0
1645 } 0
1646 ----
1647 if (!Changed) 0
1648 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
1649 ----
1650 return getLoopPassPreservedAnalyses(); 0
1651 } 0
